c hormone is typically the first hormone affected","Growth hormone deficiency rarely occurs","Gonadotropin levels remain normal","Thyroid function is usually preserved","Posterior pituitary function is always affected"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003ELymphocytic hypophysitis is an autoimmune condition that primarily affects the anterior pituitary gland. The classical pattern of hormone deficiency follows a predictable sequence:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdrenocorticotropic hormone\u003C/strong\u003E deficiency is usually the earliest and most clinically significant deficit, requiring prompt recognition and treatment\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGrowth hormone\u003C/strong\u003E deficiency commonly occurs and can affect up to 75% of patients\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGonadotropin\u003C/strong\u003E deficiency (follicle stimulating hormone and luteinising hormone) is common, leading to hypogonadism\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EThyroid function\u003C/strong\u003E is frequently affected with reduced thyroid stimulating hormone production\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior pituitary\u003C/strong\u003E  is rarely affected. When involved, DI is a common presentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EEarly recognition and hormone replacement, particularly glucocorticoids, is essential for management.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Lymphocytic hypophysitis is an autoimmune condition primarily affecting the anterior pituitary gland","Adrenocorticotropic hormone deficiency is typically the earliest and most dangerous hormonal deficiency","Glucocorticoid replacement is essential in lymphocytic hypophysitis with adrenal insufficiency"],"reference